The paper proposes a generative model based on adversarial learning for synthesizing signals composed of sinusoidal waves and random noises. This can be applied to various fields such as audio signal processing and data augmentation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
